        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down. | Bromley. | Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Dec<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. 9<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                    <salute>Dear Sclater</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have no index of Proc. Zoolog. Soc.—at least no separate one, for I have not looked through each volume,—so I sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. be very glad of both indices, &amp; they can be sent by same address as the Journal &amp;c.—<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>My list of Fellows is dated 1858; can you send me a more recent one?<ref target="#foot.f3"/></p>
<p>Some one has sent me the Intellectual Observer for December but it does not contain any article by you; hence I suppose that on Barbets is in the November No<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>.<ref target="#foot.f4"/> If I do <hi rend="doubleUnderline">not</hi> hear from you in the course of the next week, I will order the Nov<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. number.</p>
<p>A talk with you always does me good, &amp; I enjoy it much.—<ref target="#foot.f5"/></p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the reference to the article in the <hi rend="italic">Intellectual Observer</hi> (see n. 4, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD refers to two cumulative indexes to the <hi rend="italic">Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London</hi>. The index for 1830 to 1847 was published in 1866, and that for 1848 to 1860 in 1863; there is a copy of each in the collection of unbound journals in the Darwin Library–CUL.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">No list of fellows of the <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_5302.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Zoological Society of London</ref> has been found in the Darwin Library–CUL.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">CD may have received the December issue of the <hi rend="italic">Intellectual Observer</hi> with the letter of 30 November 1867 from its editor, <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4381.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Henry James Slack</ref>. Sclater’s article on barbets was published in the November issue (Sclater 1867); there is a lightly annotated copy in the Darwin Pamphlet Collection–CUL.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">CD frequently visited Sclater while in London (Lightman ed. 2004, s.v. Sclater, Philip Lutley); CD was in London from 28 November until 7 December 1867 (CD’s ‘Journal’ (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 15, Appendix II)).</note>
        </div>        
            
